Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Candente, Ferreyros, Minsur, Siderperu

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-11T19:04:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/peru-stocks-atacocha-candente-ferreyros-minsur-siderperu.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:45 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 2.4 percent to 20,630.90. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 3.1 percent to 2,703.81.  Industrial stocks slumped after U.S. stocks retreated, BBVA
Banco Continental chief analyst Miguel Leiva said in a telephone
interview.  Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based
steelmaker, dropped 2.9 percent to 2.72 soles after falling as
much as 7.5 percent.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1
PE), a unit of Gerdau SA,  Latin America ’s largest steelmaker,
fell for a third session, losing 2.7 percent to 1.42 soles.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA, slid 4.4 percent to 1.75 soles after crude declined in
New York.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor
for Caterpillar Inc., fell 4.3 percent to 3.14 soles.  Miners dropped after metals declined in New York and
 London .  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc
and lead producer, fell 2.6 percent to 1.13 soles after dropping
9.5 percent. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a
unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., dropped 4.7 percent
to $40.51.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest
tin producer, fell 3.8 percent to 3.80 soles.  Candente Copper
Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, dropped 3.8
percent to $1.51.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  